SOWETO COPS
have arrested 15 suspects who were reportedly going to rob a cash van at Kagiso
Mall. Seven of
the 15 suspects were allegedly armed when going to rob the cash van at the
mall. The cops interrupted
the suspects and a shootout ensued. Three suspects were wounded, three were
certified dead on scene and 1 of the suspects that was arrested had been wanted for
escaping from a police van. When the
suspect escaped from the van, a warrant officer who was escorting them was shot
and they disarmed him off his service pistol. No police
officer was injured during the shoot-out. The police seized
four unlicensed firearms, ammunition, 1 hijacked BMW and an Opel Astra.